14 ounce Marinara Sauce
2 ounce Diced Salami
9 ounce Tortelloni
4 ounce Peas
Salt
Pepper
Olive Oil

• Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large,
preferably nonstick, pan over medium-
high heat. Add salami and cook, stirring
occasionally, until slightly crisp, 2-3 minutes.

• Add tortelloni to pan with salami. Cook,
stirring, until tortelloni begin to warm through,
1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Carefully stir in
marinara sauce, 1⁄2 cup water (1 cup for 4
servings), and a pinch of salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tortelloni and sauce are
warmed through, 3-4 minutes.

• Stir in peas. Cook, uncovered, until peas are
warmed through and sauce has thickened
slightly, 1-2 minutes (if sauce seems too thick,
stir in additional water a splash at a time until
desired consistency is reached). Taste and
season with salt and pepper.
• Divide tortelloni between bowls and serve.